---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title='Recipes — Bryan Yao'
  description='A running ledger of recipes I cook often enough to have opinions about.'
>
  <section class='column'>
    <h1 class='display title'>Recipes</h1>
    <p class='smallcaps dek'>A running ledger.</p>

    <div class='body'>
      <p>
        Things I cook often enough to have opinions about. Tomato
        brown-butter pasta. Cast-iron ribeye with a rosemary bath. Proper
        Negroni ratios. A roast chicken that owes more to Samin Nosrat than
        to me.
      </p>
      <p>
        The list will fill in here. Kept offline for now — the cleanest form
        is still the leather notebook on the desk. Once a recipe has been
        cooked enough times to be honest about, it lands on this page.
      </p>
      <p class='smallcaps foot'>Soon: the brown butter pasta.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .column {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 6rem;
  }
  .title {
    font-size: var(--step-5);
    color: var(--ivory-hi);
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem 0;
  }
  .dek {
    color: var(--ivory-lo);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .body p {
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
    color: var(--ivory);
  }
  .body .foot {
    color: var(--ivory-lo);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }
</style>
